



=== CHAPTER 1: [Exact Chapter Title From PDF] ===



Chapter titles must be bold and clear.

Keep original wording exactly as written.

B) DIALOGUE FORMAT

Every line of dialogue must be formatted like this:





[SPEECH_BUBBLE]

CharacterName: Dialogue text exactly as written.



Example:





[SPEECH_BUBBLE]

Maya: I don't think this is a good idea.



If narration exists (no speaker), format it as:





[NARRATION]

Narration text here.



C) PLAYER CHOICES FORMAT

If the story includes decisions or choices, format them EXACTLY like this:





[CHOICE]

1. Option text exactly as written.

2. Option text exactly as written.

3. Option text exactly as written.



If a choice leads to a specific branch, format it like this:





[IF_CHOICE_1]

(dialogue that follows choice 1)



[IF_CHOICE_2]

(dialogue that follows choice 2)



Do NOT merge branches.



Keep all paths separated clearly.

D) SCENE TRANSITIONS

If the PDF shows a scene change, format it as:





--- SCENE CHANGE ---

Location: (if mentioned)

Time: (if mentioned)



E) OUTPUT FORMAT

Output as clean structured text.

No commentary.



No explanations.



No extra text.



No analysis.

Only structured dialogue-ready format.

Gemini said
